=Description=

"Isabella Lövin is a Swedish Member of the European Parliament. A member of the Green Party, she is a journalist and author of the best seller « Silent Sea » in 2007. She speaks here about how the pillaging of the sea is an example of the tragedy of the Commons and shows its relationship with land grabbing in West Africa. Interview made at the World Social Forum, Dakar, February 2011, for « The commons on the global agenda » chapter in remixthecommons.org."


